(1 comment)

I am a little unclear about what's being fixed here. 
Are we trying to be smart by switching to v2 automatically when a user configures v1 auth_url (i.e. with no version string in the url)?

Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1

I feels to me like there are two different things being talked about here.

First, handling auth v1 url.
Second, 'glance' user having access only to public images. From what I understand, this behavior is noticed on devstack. And, 
looking closely on devstack, it appears that the prefetcher is not running in admin context. The user 'glance' is probably not an admin user to begin with.

Abandoned

I see no movement on this patch. Please reopen as/when you find appropriate.
